<h2><%= message %></h2>
<section class="info-card" aria-labelledby="tool-title">
    <h1 id="tool-title">Verify PDF Certificates</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        This tool helps you confirm whether a digital certificate (PDF) is genuine.
        Each certificate contains cryptographic proof anchored on the blockchain, so
        the system can check authenticity, integrity and validity without storing your file.
    </p>

    <ul class="checks">
        <li><strong>Issuer check [manually]:</strong> Confirm the certificate was issued by a trusted organization.</li>
        <li><strong>Integrity check:</strong> Ensures the PDF content matches the record stored on the blockchain (not tampered).</li>
        <li><strong>Validity check:</strong> Verifies whether the certificate is still valid or has expired.</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="note">
        Your PDF is processed <strong>only in memory</strong> (converted to Base64) and never saved to disk. Results are displayed instantly.
    </p>

    <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="primary-btn" href="/verifier">Upload PDF</a>

        <a class="secondary-btn" href="/learn-more">How it works</a>
    </div>
</section>

